sols_latex:
From
{1(b)}
we saw that the system of equations the line must satisfy is given by

\begin{align*}
2x_1+x_2-x_3&=1\\
x_1+x_2&=1.
\end{align*}

In order to find the parametric form we solve this system. First we put
it in augmented form

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
2  &  1  &  -1  &  1\\
1  &  1  &  0  &  1
\end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

and then perform row operations to reduce the matrix. First we will swap
row 1 and row 2 so that the first pivot (row 1, column 1) has value 1.

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1  &  1  &  0  &  1\\
2  &  1  &  -1  &  1
\end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

and then we will subtract 2 multiples of row 1 from row 2 to place a
zero below the pivot,

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1  &  1  &  0  &  1\\
0  &  -1  &  -1  &  -1
\end{array}\right].
\end{align*}

We will then multiply the second row by -1 to put a 1 in the pivot
position there (row 2, column 2),

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1  &  1  &  0  &  1\\
0  &  1  &  1  &  1
\end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

and finally we will subtract 1 multiple of row 2 from row 1 to put a 0
above the pivot,

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1  &  0  &  -1  &  0\\
0  &  1  &  1  &  1
\end{array}\right].
\end{align*}

Notice that because we have more columns than rows, then we have a free
variables (the matrix is rank deficient). Let the free variable be
$x_3$, i.e. let $x_3=t$. Then from our reduced matrix problem we have
that $x_1=t$ and that $x_2+t=1$ or $x_2=1-t$. Therefore we can write
that

\begin{align*}
\begin{bmatrix}
x_1\\
x_2\\
x_3
\end{bmatrix}=
\begin{bmatrix}
0\\
1\\
0
\end{bmatrix}+
t\begin{bmatrix}
1\\
-1\\
1
\end{bmatrix}.
\end{align*}

This parametrically describes the line.
